---
<LegacyLayout
  title="Kaija's Water Safety Research HomePage"
  description="Boating safety advice from Kaija's Water Safety project."
>
<div class="mpls-legacy">
<LegacyHeader showNav />




<div class="kid-nav">
  <span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size--1 legacy-font--face-verdana"><a href="/kid/water/watersafety/">HomePage</a> | <a href="/kid/water/ski/">Water Skiing</a> | <a href="/kid/water/hypo/">Hypothermia</a> | <a href="/kid/water/ice/">Ice Safety</a> | <a href="/kid/water/boat/">Boating Safety</a> | <a href="/kid/water/denny/">Ranger Hansen</a></span>
</div>




<div class="kid-content-container">
  <table class="legacy-width-550 legacy-border-0 legacy-cellpadding-15">
    <tr> 
      <td class="legacy-width-178">
        <p><img src="/img/boat.gif" class="legacy-width-300 legacy-height-150"></p>
        <p><img src="/img/bouy.jpg" class="legacy-width-300 legacy-height-198"></p>
        <p><img src="/img/pfd.jpg" class="legacy-width-300 legacy-height-248"></p>
      </td>
      <td class="legacy-width-306"> 
        <p class="legacy-align-center"><img src="/img/jacket.gif" class="legacy-width-75 legacy-height-108"></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana"><b><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-2">How 
          can you be safe while you're boating?</span></b></span></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana"> Wear a 
          P.F.D. (Personal Flotation Device, sometimes called a life jacket) even 
          if you have been on a boat before and can swim.</span></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana"> Plan ahead 
          and check the weather forecast for the weather when you go boating or 
          go on a boating trip for the weekend or just a ride. </span></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana">You have 
          to be 16 years or older to drive a boat. To drive a boat you also have 
          to take a mail-in test that you mail in when you're done taking the 
          test. Then you're approved to drive a boat. </span></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana">It's against 
          the law if you pass a buoy if you don't read or obey the buoy. It is 
          against the law to drive a boat in a swimming area with a sign that 
          says "KEEP OUT... SWIMMING AREA".</span></p>
        <p><span class="legacy-font legacy-font--size-1 legacy-font--face-verdana">It's against 
          the law to drive a boat loaded with too many people. You can not drive 
          irresponsibly. You need to sit in the boat area and not lean over the 
          edge.</span> </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

</div>

<LegacyFooter />
</div>
</LegacyLayout>

















